<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Dr. YSR Aarogyasri Health Care Trust: Andhra Pradesh is a state-run health care programme, which provides monetary help to individuals who cannot afford a typical&nbsp;health insurance policy. This programme provides financial support to the life insured in case he/she requires funds for health-related issues. It is available in several government hospitals with coverage of upto Rs. 5 Lakh. Under this programme a health card is issued, that the beneficiary can show at the government hospitals to acquire&nbsp;cashless healthcare treatment. This scheme provides Rs. 5 Lakh of coverage to the beneficiary and his/her registered family members.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>This scheme covers in-patient care for diseases and therapies mentioned under the terms and conditions of the scheme, this scheme also provides financial support for the hospitalisation expenses. Under this scheme the beneficiary can avail free health care services from government hospitals. Dr. YSR Aarogyasri Health Care Trust scheme provides cashless treatment from first day of hospitalisation to 10 days post-discharge, this scheme also provides cashless treatment 30 days post-discharge for patients who undergo therapies.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2>Dr. YSR Aarogyasri Health Care Trust: Andhra Pradesh Eligibility Criteria</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Eligibility criteria of Dr. YSR Aarogyasri Health Care Trust: Andhra Pradesh is as mentioned below:</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul><li>The applicant must be a resident of Andhra Pradesh or Telangana</li><li>The yearly family income of the applicant’s family shall not exceed Rs. 5 Lakh</li><li>An applicant must have a ‘White Ration Card’</li><li>This scheme covers an individual whose name and photograph appears on the BPL Ration Card, this scheme also covers beneficiaries of Annapurna and Anthyodaya Anna Yojana.</li><li>Applicants should not own wet/dry land of more than 35 acres.</li><li>Applicants cannot own more than 1 car.</li><li>Applicants who are private-sector employees can also be covered under this scheme.</li></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2>Dr. YSR Aarogyasri Health Care Trust: Andhra Pradesh Benefits</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>This scheme is highly beneficial for those who want to avail quality health care services in the state of Andhra Pradesh and Telangana. Below mentioned are some benefits of Dr. YSR Aarogyasri Health Care Trust:</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul><li>This scheme offers coverage upto Rs. 5 Lakh per annum, for a family.</li><li>Provides funds for Hospitalisation expenses for mentioned diseases and therapies.</li><li>This scheme provides coverage for pre-existing medical conditions that the applicant has before enrolling themselves under this scheme. This benefit is not available under typical health insurance policies.</li><li>Follow-up treatments and check-ups are covered under this scheme.</li><li>Under this scheme, the whole family can utilise the coverage amount, one does not require a separate plan for each family member.</li></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2>Features of Dr. YSR Aarogyasri Health Care Trust: Andhra Pradesh&gt;</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Some salient features of Dr. YSR Aarogyasri Health Care Trust: Andhra Pradesh are mentioned below:</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul><li>Provides monetary help to the low-income families for the health care services required.</li><li>This scheme is available in several government hospitals with a coverage of up to Rs. 5 Lakh.</li><li>Under this scheme the beneficiary and his/her family members are covered.</li><li>This scheme provides outpatient care at health camps and government hospitals.</li><li>It covers hospitalisation expenses of the beneficiary.</li><li>Follow-up therapies and procedures are covered under this scheme.</li><li>This scheme provides cashless treatment from the first day of hospitalisation to 10 days post-discharge.</li><li>Under this scheme cashless treatment 30 days, post-discharge is provided for patients who undergo therapies.</li></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2>How to Enroll for Dr. YSR Aarogyasri Health Care Trust: Andhra Pradesh?</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>One can enroll for Dr. YSR Aarogyasri Health Care Trust: Andhra Pradesh online and offline. Below mentioned are two to enroll under Dr. YSR Aarogyasri Health Care Trust:</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>1. Offline Method</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Follow these simple steps to register under Dr. YSR Aarogyasri Health Care Trust scheme via offline method:</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Step 1-&nbsp;</strong>Visit the official YSR Navasakam website</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Step 2-&nbsp;</strong>Select the ‘Downloads’ tab displayed on the website</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Step 3-&nbsp;</strong>Click on ‘YSR Aarogyasri Health Card Performa’, download and print the application form.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Step 4-&nbsp;</strong>Submit the duly filled form, along with supporting documents at the nearest enrollment centre.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Step 5-</strong>&nbsp;Wait for the application to be accepted, after which the YSR Health Card shall be issued.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>2. Online Method</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Below mentioned are the instructions to register for Dr. Aarogyasri Health Care Trust online:</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Step 1-&nbsp;</strong>Visit any of the 2 mentioned websites - the official YSR Navasakam website or the gram ward Sachivalayam Portal and log in.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Step 2-</strong>&nbsp;After logging in, click on the ‘Aarogyasri Health Card’ application form.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Step 3-</strong>&nbsp;Fill up the application form carefully and submit the form by attaching the supporting documents. Print out the application for future reference.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2>Documents Required for Dr. YSR Aarogyasri Health Care Trust: Andhra Pradesh</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Below mentioned is the list of essential documents required for the application of Dr. YSR Aarogyasri Health Care Trust:</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul><li>Aadhaar Card</li><li>Address Proof</li><li>Income Certificate/Income Tax Returns</li></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->
